-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705183,"age":22,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705184,"age":32,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705185,"age":42,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Adam d'Alditheley was born about 1064, in Staffordshire, England, his father, Gamel de Tettesworth, was 23 and his mother, De Mottran, was 20. He married Mabella Stoneley in 1082, in Audley, Staffordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died about 1128, in Audley, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 66."},"et":{"abt 1064–Abt 1128":"umbes 1064–umbes 1128","1057–1128":"1057–1128","1063–Male":"1063–Surnud","1064–1128":"1064–1128","1065–Male":"1065–Surnud","–1160":"–1160","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1083–1132":"1083–1132","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","1088–1205":"1088–1205","1043–1086":"1043–1086","1045–Female":"1045–Surnud","1088":"1088","Abt 1128":"umbes 1128","1066":"1066","1132":"1132","1043":"1043","1065":"1065","abt 1064":"umbes 1064","1086":"1086","1130":"1130"